Both Drip Footwear and Sekhukhune United confirmed a partnership agreement on Tuesday morning. The South African entrepreneur and founder of Drip Footwear, Lekau Sehoana, took to Twitter to announce that the company is now the official sponsor of Sekhukhune United Football Club. The famous footwear brand will become the official sneaker supplier for Babina Noko. This deal will see the recognised sneaker brand supplying the club with all Babina Noko’s sneaker requirements. The team members will wear Drip-branded sneakers on all official club duties. “We could not have asked for a better partner than Drip Footwear to fulfil our sneaker needs for our club. This brand is one of the fastest-growing in southern Africa. Their bold design, versatility and collaborative culture are what make them stand out. These attributes resonate deeply with Babina Noko, as we are a club that aspire to the same high standards.
“We are delighted to establish this partnership with Drip Footwear and we look forward to a prosperous and mutually beneficial relationship,” said the club’s chairperson, Simon Malatji. Sehoana said 2022 is a year dedicated to the immense work of collaborations and building partnerships. “May the partnership with Sekhukhune United continue to embody greatness.”